sd.PT_NAME: Loss of personal independence in daily activities

freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Severe nasal congestion, sneezing, and runny nose not responding well to OTC medications or antibiotics.  Unclear if underlying ENT/sinus issue, immunology issue, or due to CPAP machine.

Significantly ill on 21 Feb 2021 with severe nasal congestion and constant clear rhinorrhea not significantly relieved with antihistamines or OTC cold medicines.  Stayed in bed all day and most of next day, not improved until 24 Feb, then relapsed.

Still having episodes of significant nasal congestion and rhinorrhea that impact daily activities and require medication.  Awoke with a headache this morning, with persistent pressure in head and sinuses.
